# LaborLens Analytics

Independent research project analyzing AI adoption trends and labor market
outcomes across industries using CPS ASEC microdata and Census BTOS data.

## Research Questions

1. Do workers in AI-exposed occupations earn a wage premium in NAICS 54?
2. Which subsectors are seeing the fastest AI adoption (BTOS)?
3. Has the AI wage premium grown from 2020 to 2025?

## Data Sources

| Source | Coverage | Variables |
|--------|----------|-----------|
| IPUMS CPS ASEC | 2020–2025, NAICS 54 | Earnings, hours, occupation, education, age |
| Census BTOS Subsector | Mid-2025–Mid-2026 | AI adoption % by subsector (Q7, Q24) |

## Methods

- **Mincer earnings regression** — OLS on log(EARNWEEK) controlling for AI exposure, education, age, year fixed effects
- **AI wage premium** — exp(β_AI) - 1 = % earnings premium for AI-exposed occupations
- **Trend analysis** — median earnings by occupation × year (2020–2025)
- **BTOS adoption delta** — earliest vs latest biweekly period AI adoption % change

## Occupational Exposure Groups

**AI-Exposed** (Stanford AI Index high-intensity):
- Software Developers, Engineers, QA
- Computer Programmers
- Cybersecurity Analysts
- Database Administrators
- Network/Systems Analysts

**Comparison** (NAICS 54, lower AI exposure):
- Lawyers, Paralegals
- Accountants/Auditors
- Architects, Civil Engineers
- Chief Executives, IS Managers

